-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Juli 17, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104ord1665702918167.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ord1665702918167.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ord1665702918167.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"ord1665702918167\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Converts data from the format with which Uniface supplies it to the connector, to a\n      specified connector-level packing code.</p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"ord1665702918167__topic_d131165e1_d131166e1_d131167e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ord1665702918167__p_d131168e1_d131169e1_d131170e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">short udbconv</code>(<var class=\"keyword varname\">uc, src, dst, len, flist, pack</var>)</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ord1665702918167__p_d131171e1_d131172e1_d131173e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">struct uctrl</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">*uc</var>;</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ord1665702918167__p_d131174e1_d131175e1_d131176e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">unsigned char</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">*src</var>;</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ord1665702918167__p_d131177e1_d131178e1_d131179e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">unsigned char</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">*dst</var>;</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ord1665702918167__p_d131180e1_d131181e1_d131182e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">short</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">len</var>;</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ord1665702918167__p_d131183e1_d131184e1_d131185e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">struct ufldlst</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">*flist</var>;</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ord1665702918167__p_d131186e1_d131187e1_d131188e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">short</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">pack</var>;</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ord1665702918167__section_k1p_1qs_gwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d994795e117\">Parameters</h2>\n<dl class=\"dl parml\" id=\"ord1665702918167__parml_eht_dqs_gwb\">\n<dt class=\"dt pt dlterm\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">uc</var></dt>\n<dd class=\"dd pd\">Address of the current control block.</dd>\n<dt class=\"dt pt dlterm\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">src</var></dt>\n<dd class=\"dd pd\">Pointer to the data to be converted.</dd>\n<dt class=\"dt pt dlterm\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">dst</var></dt>\n<dd class=\"dd pd\">Pointer to a buffer in which to store the result. The connector must define this\n                  buffer.</dd>\n<dt class=\"dt pt dlterm\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">len</var></dt>\n<dd class=\"dd pd\">Length of the data pointed to by <var class=\"keyword varname\">src</var>.\n                  <var class=\"keyword varname\">flist</var>. An entry in the <code class=\"ph codeph\">ufldlst</code> structure\n                  describing the field to be converted. </dd>\n<dt class=\"dt pt dlterm\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">pack</var></dt>\n<dd class=\"dd pd\">Connector-level packing code to which to convert.<p class=\"p\" id=\"ord1665702918167__p_d131192e1_d131193e1_d131194e1\">If <var class=\"keyword varname\">pack</var> is zero, the\n                     following defaults are used:</p><div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"ord1665702918167__table_d15695e1_d15696e1_d15697e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Default connector-level packing codes</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"ord1665702918167__table_d15695e1_d15696e1_d15697e1__entry__1\">Data type</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"ord1665702918167__table_d15695e1_d15696e1_d15697e1__entry__2\">Default packing code</th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ord1665702918167__table_d15695e1_d15696e1_d15697e1__entry__1\">B</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ord1665702918167__table_d15695e1_d15696e1_d15697e1__entry__2\">B2</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ord1665702918167__table_d15695e1_d15696e1_d15697e1__entry__1\">D</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ord1665702918167__table_d15695e1_d15696e1_d15697e1__entry__2\">D3</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ord1665702918167__table_d15695e1_d15696e1_d15697e1__entry__1\">E</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ord1665702918167__table_d15695e1_d15696e1_d15697e1__entry__2\">E4</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ord1665702918167__table_d15695e1_d15696e1_d15697e1__entry__1\">F</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ord1665702918167__table_d15695e1_d15696e1_d15697e1__entry__2\">N20</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ord1665702918167__table_d15695e1_d15696e1_d15697e1__entry__1\">N</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ord1665702918167__table_d15695e1_d15696e1_d15697e1__entry__2\">N20</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ord1665702918167__table_d15695e1_d15696e1_d15697e1__entry__1\">T</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ord1665702918167__table_d15695e1_d15696e1_d15697e1__entry__2\">T1</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div></dd>\n</dl>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ord1665702918167__section_ifn_nqs_gwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d994795e272\">Return values</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ord1665702918167__p_d131198e1_d131199e1_d131200e1\">The length of the converted data.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ord1665702918167__section_yth_1pz_bcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d994795e281\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">Converts data from the format with which Uniface supplies it to the connector, to a\n            specified connector-level packing code.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ord1665702918167__p_d131207e1_d131208e1_d131209e1\">For example, <code class=\"ph codeph\">udbconv</code> can be used\n            to convert binary data in the if list to ASCII string format when a SQL query must be\n            constructed.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ord1665702918167__p_d131210e1_d131211e1_d131212e1\">The following example converts data from an input\n            buffer called InputData to ASCII. The variable <var class=\"keyword varname\">FieldNumber</var> contains\n            the number of the field to convert.</p>\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104ord1665702918167_html_0\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"ord1665702918167__codeblock_f2f_tqs_gwb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">ConvertData ( struct uctrl *ControlBlock,\nunsigned char *InputData,\nshort FieldNumber )\n{\nshort LengthIn, LengthOut;\nunsigned char Buffer[MAX_BUF];\nstruct ufldlst *FieldList;\nFieldList = (struct ufldlst *)ControlBlock-&gt;ufldlst + FieldNumber + 1;\n/* +1 because first entry is dummy. */\nLengthIn = strlen ( InputData );\nLengthOut = udbconv ( ControlBlock, InputData,\n(unsigned char *)Buffer,\nLengthIn, FieldList, pN20 );\n}</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2530706\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2530706\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "udbconv Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Juli 17, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Converts data from the format with which Uniface supplies it to the connector, to a specified connector-level packing code. short udbconv ( uc, src, dst, len, flist, pack ) struct uctrl *uc ; unsigned char *src ; unsigned char *dst ; short len ; struct ufldlst *flist ; short pack ; Parameters uc Address of the current control block. src Pointer to the data to be converted. dst Pointer to a buffer in which to store the result. The connector must define this buffer. len Length of the data pointed to by src . flist . An entry in the ufldlst structure describing the field to be converted. pack Connector-level packing code to which to convert. If pack is zero, the following defaults are used: Table 1. Default connector-level packing codes Data type Default packing code B B2 D D3 E E4 F N20 N N20 T T1 Return values The length of the converted data. Description Converts data from the format with which Uniface supplies it to the connector, to a specified connector-level packing code. For example, udbconv can be used to convert binary data in the if list to ASCII string format when a SQL query must be constructed. The following example converts data from an input buffer called InputData to ASCII. The variable FieldNumber contains the number of the field to convert. Explain this code ConvertData ( struct uctrl *ControlBlock, unsigned char *InputData, short FieldNumber ) { short LengthIn, LengthOut; unsigned char Buffer[MAX_BUF]; struct ufldlst *FieldList; FieldList = (struct ufldlst *)ControlBlock->ufldlst + FieldNumber + 1; /* +1 because first entry is dummy. */ LengthIn = strlen ( InputData ); LengthOut = udbconv ( ControlBlock, InputData, (unsigned char *)Buffer, LengthIn, FieldList, pN20 ); } Copy Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}